AfrAsia Bank Expects Loans to Increase 58% This Fiscal Year

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-09-20T13:42:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/afrasia-bank-expects-loans-to-increase-58-this-fiscal-year.html
AfrAsia Bank, a closely held
Mauritian bank that lends to companies, expects its loan book to
rise 60 percent to 13.5 billion rupees ($470 million) for its
financial year through June 2012, Chief Executive Officer James
Benoit said.  “We expect loans to grow by another 58 percent during the
year,” Benoit said in an e-mailed response to questions today.
Loans surged 76 percent to 8.56 billion rupees for the 12 months
through June, the Port Louis-based lender said in an e-mailed
statement.  AfrAsia Bank , which started operations in 2007, said its
annual profit more than tripled to 124.4 million rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
